#### Q58. Which code example creates the string "Hello Mars" in storage buffer `hello`.

-  :

```c
    char hello[25];
    strcpy(hello, "Hello ");
    strcpy(hello, "Mars");
```

-  :

```c
    char hello[25];
    char *p;
    strcpy(hello, "Hello World");
    p = hello;
    p +=6;
    strcpy(p, "Mars");
```

-  :

```c
    char *hello;
    strcpy(hello, "Hello World");
    hello+=6;
    strcpy(hello, "Mars");
```

-  :

```c
    char hello[25];
    strcpy(hello, "Hello World");
    strcpy(*hello[6], "Mars");
```
